The '''false tagging theory (FTT)''' is a [[neuroanatomical]] theory which posits that the [[prefrontal cortex]] is critical for doubting (initially believed) cognitive representations in the [[postrolandic]] cortexes.<ref>{{cite book|title=Principles of Frontal Lobe Function|date=2013|publisher=Oxford University Press|location=New York|isbn=9780199837755|pages=383–416|author=Asp, EW|edition=2nd|author2=Tranel, D|editor=Stuss, DT |editor2=Knight, RT|chapter=Ch. 24}}</ref>  This theory was developed by Erik Asp.

